cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper discusses deep neural networks and their performance in various tasks, suggesting that their generalization is flawed due to phenomena such as adversarial and fooling examples. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on deep learning architectures and their properties, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV.
